<paragraph id="355ED367FF9E8D513B9FFB6DFF5FFAC7" blockId="7.[145,761,1273,1387]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513B9FFB6DFD13FAA3" box="[145,661,1273,1295]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">
<typeStatus id="EA5A6DC5FF9E8D513B9FFB6DFF4CFAA3" box="[145,202,1274,1295]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513A4CFB6EFD13FAA3" authorityName="Budde-Lund" authorityYear="1885" box="[322,661,1273,1295]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Armadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muricatum">Armadillidium muricatum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
Budde- Lund, 1885, by original designation. Originally described as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513ACCFAA1FF52FAC7" authority="(Arcangeli, 1935)" baseAuthorityName="Arcangeli" baseAuthorityYear="1935" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Armadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513ACCFAA1FDF2FAE7" box="[450,628,1334,1355]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">Armadillidium</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5170AE96FF9E8D51398FFAA1FF4FFAC7" author="Arcangeli A" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" pagination="171 - 195" refId="ref16538" refString="Arcangeli A. 1935. Isopodi terrestri di caverne della Spagna (Collezione del Museo di Storia Naturale di Madrid). Eos, Revista Espanola de Entomologia 10: 171 - 195." type="journal article" year="1935">Arcangeli, 1935</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="355ED367FF9E8D513B9FFA03FBF3FE7C" blockId="7.[145,762,1428,1879]" lastBlockId="7.[809,1426,197,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513B9FFA03FE96FA05" box="[145,272,1428,1449]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="5170AE96FF9E8D513AC7FA03FD13FA06" author="Arcangeli A" box="[457,661,1428,1450]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" pagination="133 - 151" refId="ref16572" refString="Arcangeli A. 1936. Sopra alcuni sottogeneri di Armadillidium Br. (Isopodi terrestri). Bollettino dei Musei di Zoologia ed Anatomia comparata della reale Universita di Torino 45: 133 - 151." type="journal article" year="1936">Arcangeli (1936)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5170AE96FF9E8D5139ABFA03FF72FA64" author="Vandel A" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" pagination="61 - 66" refId="ref19504" refString="Vandel A. 1954 a. Une nouvelle espece cavernicole appartenant a la famille des Armadillidiidae et provenant de l'Espagne orientale. Notes Biospeologiques 9: 61 - 66." type="journal article" year="1954">Vandel (1954a)</bibRefCitation>
and the new species here described, 
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513B9FFA46FEFEFA4A" authorityName="Arcangeli" authorityYear="1935" box="[145,376,1489,1510]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Cristarmadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513B9FFA46FEFEFA4A" box="[145,376,1489,1510]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">Cristarmadillidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed by their 
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513961FA46FD3BFA4A" authorityName="Budde-Lund" authorityYear="1885" box="[623,701,1489,1510]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Eluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513961FA46FD3BFA4A" box="[623,701,1489,1510]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">Eluma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<typeStatus id="EA5A6DC5FF9E8D5139C8FA45FD7FFA4B" box="[710,761,1490,1511]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">type</typeStatus>
head, reduced eye size (from four to six ommatidia in 
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513B9FF998FEE2F98F" authorityName="Recuero &amp; Rodríguez-Flores &amp; García-París" authorityYear="2022" box="[145,356,1550,1572]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Cristarmadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myrmecophilum">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513B9FF998FEE2F98F" box="[145,356,1550,1572]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">C.myrmecophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
totento 
<quantity id="F2197E82FF9E8D513AB0F998FE74F988" box="[446,498,1550,1572]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.048" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" unit="in" value="12.0">12in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513AFAF998FD0BF988" authorityName="Budde-Lund" authorityYear="1885" box="[500,653,1551,1572]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Armadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muricatum">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513AFAF998FD0BF988" box="[500,653,1551,1572]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">C.muricatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
),absence of clear sexual dimorphism in pereopod 7, presence (
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513B97F9DBFEF2F9CD" authorityName="Recuero &amp; Rodríguez-Flores &amp; García-París" authorityYear="2022" box="[153,372,1612,1633]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Cristarmadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myrmecophilum">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513B97F9DBFEF2F9CD" box="[153,372,1612,1633]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">C. myrmecophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or not (
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513AD7F9DBFDFFF9CD" authorityName="Budde-Lund" authorityYear="1885" box="[473,633,1612,1633]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Armadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muricatum">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513AD7F9DBFDFFF9CD" box="[473,633,1612,1633]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">C. muricatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513989F9DBFD74F9CD" authorityName="Vandel" authorityYear="1954" box="[647,754,1612,1633]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Cristarmadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breuili">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513989F9DBFD74F9CD" box="[647,754,1612,1633]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">C. breuili</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513B9FF9FDFF4AF932" authority="Cifuentes &amp; Prieto, 2020" authorityName="Cifuentes &amp; Prieto" authorityYear="2020" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Cristarmadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaragozai">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513B9FF9FDFD84F92C" box="[145,514,1642,1664]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">Cristarmadillidium zaragozai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5170AE96FF9E8D513902F9FDFF4AF932" author="Cifuentes J &amp; Prieto CE" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" pagination="111" refId="ref17111" refString="Cifuentes J, Prieto CE. 2020. Cristarmadillidium zaragozai n. sp. (Oniscidea, Armadillidiidae), un nuevo isopodo terrestre de la Peninsula Iberica. Graellsia 76: e 111." type="journal article" year="2020">Cifuentes &amp; Prieto, 2020</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513A01F91EFF4DF911" authority="Cifuentes, 2021" authorityName="Cifuentes" authorityYear="2021" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Cristarmadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alticola">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513A01F91EFDF6F932" box="[271,624,1673,1694]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">Cristarmadillidium alticola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5170AE96FF9E8D513974F91EFF4DF911" author="Cifuentes J" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" pagination="61 - 72" refId="ref17059" refString="Cifuentes J. 2021. El genero Cristarmadillidium Arcangeli, 1935, en la peninsula iberica, y descripcion de una nueva especie C. alticola n. sp. de Sierra Nevada (Oniscidea, Armadillidiidae). Boletin de la Asociacion Espanola de Entomologia 45: 61 - 72." type="journal article" year="2021">Cifuentes, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) of a small schisma in pereonite 1 epimera; tubercles developed (
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513A8AF950FDA2F970" authorityName="Budde-Lund" authorityYear="1885" box="[388,548,1735,1756]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Armadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muricatum">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513A8AF950FDA2F970" box="[388,548,1735,1756]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">C. muricatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513952F950FD6CF970" authorityName="Cifuentes &amp; Prieto" authorityYear="2020" box="[604,746,1735,1756]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Cristarmadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaragozai">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513952F950FD6CF970" box="[604,746,1735,1756]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">C. zaragozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), obsolete (
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513A1FF972FE0AF956" authorityName="Vandel" authorityYear="1954" box="[273,396,1765,1786]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Cristarmadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breuili">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513A1FF972FE0AF956" box="[273,396,1765,1786]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">C. breuili</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513ADBF972FD4EF956" authorityName="Recuero &amp; Rodríguez-Flores &amp; García-París" authorityYear="2022" box="[469,712,1765,1786]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Cristarmadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myrmecophilum">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513ADBF972FD4EF956" box="[469,712,1765,1786]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">C. myrmecophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or absent (
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF9E8D513BF6F893FEFDF8B5" authorityName="Cifuentes" authorityYear="2021" box="[248,379,1796,1817]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Cristarmadillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alticola">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513BF6F893FEFDF8B5" box="[248,379,1796,1817]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">C. alticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); outer margin of pereonite 2 epimera straight; shape of distal part of pereonite 4 epimera narrow and rounded, of pereonite 5 epimera rounded, broader than 4 but narrower than other epimera; large areas of pereon, pleon and epimera, and of telson and uropod exopods, covered by rounded, concave papillae (but see 
<bibRefCitation id="5170AE96FF9E8D513FEDFEB6FA06FE9A" author="Garcia L" box="[1251,1408,289,311]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref17513" refString="Garcia L. 2020. Algunas observaciones morfologicas sobre Cristarmadillidium breuili Vandel, 1954 (Oniscidea: Armadillidiidae) del Complejo del Arroyo de la Rambla (Peal de Becerro, Jaen). Monografias Bioespeleologicas 15: 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="2020">Garcia, 2020</bibRefCitation>
); glandular fields in pereonites 2 and 3 epimera transversely elongated, located far from the lateral margin, medially in epimera 2, submedially in epimera 3; and pleopod 2 exopod only slightly longer (1.11–1.30 times) than wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="355ED367FF9E8D513827FE6EFC5CFC8E" blockId="7.[809,1426,505,803]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF9E8D513827FE6EFC12FDA2" box="[809,916,505,526]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">Remarks:</emphasis>
The tegument microstructures resembling rounded, concave papillae, which are present on large areas of the body surface (
<figureCitation id="ADDACFE2FF9E8D513F6AFDA1FB67FDE0" box="[1124,1249,566,588]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="8.[163,244,1675,1697]" captionTargetBox="[285,1321,195,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-26@8.[285,1321,195,1635]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 5. Scanning electron photomicrographs showing the general habitus of Iberiarmadillidium psammophilum (A), Iberiarmadillidium pinicola (B), Iberiarmadillidium sakura (C), Cristarmadillidium myrmecophilum (D) and Cristarmadillidium muricatum (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6459250" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6459250/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="1319">Figs 5D, E</figureCitation>
, 
